The paper deals with data cleaning and integrity constraints, which are typically studied in the database community (cs.DB). The use of approximate dependencies and the formulation of the problem as a constraint optimization problem suggest a machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS) perspective. The dynamic programming algorithm and the optimization of performance over large datasets are also relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DC). Finally, the use of real-world datasets suggests a practical application focus, which could fall under machine learning or data management (cs.LG).
